  }
  visual_effects {
    rating: "Good to Very Good"
    comments: "Visual Effects (This movie is really about the visual effects as it helps bring to life the world, the monsters, and their fight scenes)"
  }
  pacing: "Pacing is incredibly slow as this movie feels like it drags (the first hour just feels like exposition); the runtime could've been 20 minutes longer to help show the relationship between Godzilla and Kong because it is very forced"
  climax: "Climax is very short even though it is well executed (Godzilla and Kong are only in the movie for like 20 minutes together)"
  tone: "Tone is just a stereotypical action monster movie (very Michael Bay-like)"
  final_notes: "This movie is Kong ft Godzilla because the two are only on-screen together for like 20 minutes and their relationship is super forced"
  overall: "Overall, a very stupid movie that has a dumb plot because the movie just feels like Kong ft Godzilla, but has some merit in watching with its visual effects, cinematography, and grand monster-filled fight scenes"
